<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,1826]" box="[198,1436,772,799]" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,358,772,798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Local Name:</emphasis>
–– 
<emphasis box="[388,576,773,798]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Pinang Nyaring</emphasis>
and/or 
<emphasis box="[665,863,773,798]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Pinang Bandang</emphasis>
(local dialect in 
<collectingRegion box="[1060,1293,773,799]" country="Indonesia" name="Kalimantan Tengah" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Central Kalimantan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1424,773,799]" name="Indonesia" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,1826]" box="[198,454,809,835]" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,255,809,835]" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Uses</emphasis>
:––Not recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,152,1826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,456,845,871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Conservation status:</emphasis>
––Near Threatened (NT). The extent of occurrence of this species is a large triangle that includes part of 
<collectingRegion box="[397,631,882,908]" country="Indonesia" name="Kalimantan Tengah" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Central Kalimantan</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[647,768,882,908]" name="Indonesia" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
), Lambir National Park (
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1172,882,908]" name="Malaysia" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Sarawak</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1295,882,908]" name="Malaysia" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
) and Ladan Hills Forest Reserve in Lamunin, 
<collectingRegion box="[560,645,919,945]" country="Brunei" name="Tutong" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Tutong</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[662,900,919,945]" name="Brunei" pageId="7" pageNumber="13">Brunei Darussalam</collectingCountry>
). However, it is known only from three wild localities, only two of which are protected. In Lambir, the species was observed to be rare. It is anticipated that this species will become increasingly threatened. Detailed population studies are needed to assess its conservation status more precisely.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
